entries.meaning: (archaic, poetic) A peeping or glancing outward.
examples: A blithe lass was she on the first day of the new year, but a blithe lass was she ten days thereafter, as, at the first outpeep of the grey wintry dawn, she stole from her sleepless pillow to take a last virgin look of her father's garden  [â€¦]
